.TH SINGINE-SINGE 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-singe \- render governed @mentions and inspect the people registry
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine singe
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B singe
command resolves @mentions against the local people registry and renders them
into display names, email addresses, URNs, or other governed identity forms.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B render
Render a template string or stdin content, replacing @mentions.
.TP
.B people
List all people in the registry.
.TP
.B who \fIMENTION\fR
Resolve one @mention and print its details.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine singe render "Ask @si to review this"
singine singe render --fmt email "Contact @si and @stal"
singine singe people --json
singine singe who @si
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1)
